<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1326,622,1291]" box="[312,666,783,809]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Adult male (n = 1) (
<figureCitation box="[546,657,783,809]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[301,1257,341,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[300,1262,329,1720]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., male adult. 1. antenna. 2. apical flagellomeres. 3. palpomeres II–V. 4. lateral view of scutum. 5. wing, Dc — dorsocentrals, H — humerals, Prs — prescutellars, and Pa — prealars. 6. tibial spurs. 7. hypopygium, left: ventral and internal views, right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030411/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs. 1–7</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1326,622,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Body length 
<quantity box="[467,577,823,849]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.36" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="3.36">3.36 mm</quantity>
; wing 
<quantity box="[658,764,823,849]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.64" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="1.64">1.64 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[843,949,823,849]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
wide. Head brown; thorax yellowish brown, with mesonotum and episternum dark brown; wings grayish; legs and abdominal tergites brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1326,622,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Head. Temporal setae 16, clypeals 4. Antenna with 14 flagellomeres (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1228,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[301,1257,341,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[300,1262,329,1720]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., male adult. 1. antenna. 2. apical flagellomeres. 3. palpomeres II–V. 4. lateral view of scutum. 5. wing, Dc — dorsocentrals, H — humerals, Prs — prescutellars, and Pa — prealars. 6. tibial spurs. 7. hypopygium, left: ventral and internal views, right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030411/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), Fm14 
<quantity box="[264,342,983,1009]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="52.0">52 µm</quantity>
, Fm13 
<quantity box="[430,523,983,1009]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="165.0">165 µm</quantity>
, Fm1–12 
<quantity box="[640,731,983,1009]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.97" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="697.0">697 µm</quantity>
long; AR = 0.31; apical flagellomeres as in 
<figureCitation box="[1249,1321,983,1009]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[301,1257,341,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[300,1262,329,1720]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., male adult. 1. antenna. 2. apical flagellomeres. 3. palpomeres II–V. 4. lateral view of scutum. 5. wing, Dc — dorsocentrals, H — humerals, Prs — prescutellars, and Pa — prealars. 6. tibial spurs. 7. hypopygium, left: ventral and internal views, right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030411/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
. Palp as in 
<figureCitation box="[385,456,1023,1049]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[301,1257,341,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[300,1262,329,1720]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., male adult. 1. antenna. 2. apical flagellomeres. 3. palpomeres II–V. 4. lateral view of scutum. 5. wing, Dc — dorsocentrals, H — humerals, Prs — prescutellars, and Pa — prealars. 6. tibial spurs. 7. hypopygium, left: ventral and internal views, right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030411/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
; palpomere lengths 2–5: 
<quantity box="[752,831,1023,1049]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="32.0">32 µm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[843,936,1023,1049]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.16" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="116.0">116 µm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[948,1027,1023,1049]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="84.0">84 µm</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[1040,1119,1023,1049]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="80.0">80 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1326,622,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Thorax. Antepronotals 6; acrostichals about 40, biserial; dorsocentral (Dc), humeral (H), prescutellar (Pr), and prealar (Pa) setation as in 
<figureCitation box="[876,947,1103,1129]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[301,1257,341,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[300,1262,329,1720]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., male adult. 1. antenna. 2. apical flagellomeres. 3. palpomeres II–V. 4. lateral view of scutum. 5. wing, Dc — dorsocentrals, H — humerals, Prs — prescutellars, and Pa — prealars. 6. tibial spurs. 7. hypopygium, left: ventral and internal views, right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030411/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
; scutellars 6; postnotals absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1326,622,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[392,464,1143,1169]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[301,1257,341,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[300,1262,329,1720]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., male adult. 1. antenna. 2. apical flagellomeres. 3. palpomeres II–V. 4. lateral view of scutum. 5. wing, Dc — dorsocentrals, H — humerals, Prs — prescutellars, and Pa — prealars. 6. tibial spurs. 7. hypopygium, left: ventral and internal views, right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030411/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Membrane without setae, with microtrichia. VR 0.92. Brachiolum with 5 setae, 
<collectionCode box="[359,378,1183,1209]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">R</collectionCode>
with 27, squama with 5. Costa extended 
<quantity box="[864,955,1183,1209]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="120.0">120 µm</quantity>
beyond apex of 
<collectionCode box="[1150,1169,1183,1209]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="right" box="[1175,1206,1195,1212]" fontSize="7" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">4+5</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
