<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1702,1848]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Hypopygium (
<figureCitation box="[484,557,1702,1728]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[301,1257,341,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[300,1262,329,1720]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., male adult. 1. antenna. 2. apical flagellomeres. 3. palpomeres II–V. 4. lateral view of scutum. 5. wing, Dc — dorsocentrals, H — humerals, Prs — prescutellars, and Pa — prealars. 6. tibial spurs. 7. hypopygium, left: ventral and internal views, right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030411/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite length 
<quantity box="[807,901,1702,1728]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="150.0">150 µm</quantity>
, gonostylus 
<quantity box="[1050,1131,1702,1728]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="62.0">62 µm</quantity>
; HV 2.4. Gonostylus simple, not differentiated into lobes; megaseta of apical lobe 
<quantity box="[1055,1131,1742,1768]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 µm</quantity>
long; P, x and y setae present, but not conspicuous. Genitalic apodemes as in 
<figureCitation box="[977,1047,1782,1808]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[301,1257,341,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[300,1262,329,1720]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., male adult. 1. antenna. 2. apical flagellomeres. 3. palpomeres II–V. 4. lateral view of scutum. 5. wing, Dc — dorsocentrals, H — humerals, Prs — prescutellars, and Pa — prealars. 6. tibial spurs. 7. hypopygium, left: ventral and internal views, right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030411/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
; phallapodemes in longitudinal, mesal position, with distal portions protruded outside the hypopygium.
</paragraph>
