(n = 1) (
<figureCitation box="[480,604,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–11" captionStartId="3.[264,383,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,321,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-57@3.[312,1274,315,1704]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–11. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., pupa. 8. frontal apotome. 9. thoracic horn; A. pores, B. aeropyles, and C. external membrane of thoracic horn. 10. thorax. 11. abdominal segments, left: ventral view (SI and SII not preserved), right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030413/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 8–11</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,283,790]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Exuviae pale, mesonotum with median­lateral and posterior brownish spots. Total length 
<quantity box="[344,437,364,390]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
. Frontal apotome and prefrons as in 
<figureCitation box="[864,935,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–11" captionStartId="3.[264,383,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,321,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-57@3.[312,1274,315,1704]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–11. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., pupa. 8. frontal apotome. 9. thoracic horn; A. pores, B. aeropyles, and C. external membrane of thoracic horn. 10. thorax. 11. abdominal segments, left: ventral view (SI and SII not preserved), right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030413/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
. Thoracic horn as in 
<figureCitation box="[1181,1251,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–11" captionStartId="3.[264,383,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,321,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-57@3.[312,1274,315,1704]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–11. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., pupa. 8. frontal apotome. 9. thoracic horn; A. pores, B. aeropyles, and C. external membrane of thoracic horn. 10. thorax. 11. abdominal segments, left: ventral view (SI and SII not preserved), right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030413/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
. Plastron plate of thoracic horn large, rounded, triangular, 
<quantity box="[916,1009,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="240.0">240 µm</quantity>
long by 
<quantity box="[1124,1218,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="208.0">208 µm</quantity>
greatest width, with closely set and densely arranged pores. External membrane of thoracic horn with elongate, sharply pointed polygonal mesh. Respiratory atrium opening to plastron through 4 aeropyles; 3 short precorneals. Thoracic setation as in 
<figureCitation box="[1052,1141,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–11" captionStartId="3.[264,383,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,321,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-57@3.[312,1274,315,1704]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–11. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., pupa. 8. frontal apotome. 9. thoracic horn; A. pores, B. aeropyles, and C. external membrane of thoracic horn. 10. thorax. 11. abdominal segments, left: ventral view (SI and SII not preserved), right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030413/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
; distance from Dc1–3 to Dc4 about 
<quantity box="[512,608,564,590]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="220.0">220 µm</quantity>
. Posterior angles of abdominal segments III–VIII protracted into large transverse processes ending in sharp, straight points. Abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[294,377,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–11" captionStartId="3.[264,383,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[318,1268,321,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-57@3.[312,1274,315,1704]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–11. Podonomus pepinellii sp. n., pupa. 8. frontal apotome. 9. thoracic horn; A. pores, B. aeropyles, and C. external membrane of thoracic horn. 10. thorax. 11. abdominal segments, left: ventral view (SI and SII not preserved), right: dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5030413/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
(sternites I and II are incomplete). Abdominal segments VIII and IX with 6 and 5 macrosetae, respectively; anal spur reduced.
</paragraph>
